Federico Javier Santander Mereles, (born 4 June 1991 in San Lorenzo) is a Paraguayan footballer who plays for Racing Club in the Argentine Primera Divisin. Santander started in the youth divisions of Guaran where he excelled and was part of the under-20 squad that won the international friendly championship held in Valencia, Spain. After winning the U20 tournament with Guaran he attracted the interest of several clubs and had a trial with AC Milan of Italy.[1] In 2008, at the age of 16, he made his debut with the senior squad of Guaran by scoring a goal in the 5-2 rout against Tacuary.[2] On 31 August 2010, He sign to the French Toulouse FC. On February 2012, he was signed to Racing Club for 3 years contract with purchase option for 20% of his sports rights.[3] On 28 September 2009, at the 2009 FIFA U-20 World Cup in Egypt, Santander scored the first goal for the Paraguay U-20 squad against home team Egypt, giving the Paraguayans a 1-0 lead. Wearing the number 9 as a replacement for Roque Santa Cruz, he debuted for Paraguay on October 9, 2010 in a 1-0 loss against Australia in Sydney.[4] 
